  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (dbd935b 2023-10-17T06:28:15.598998000Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nThere seems to be a bug that very random whenever I try to run unit tests the error seems to occur here\r\n\r\n``rust\r\n  JournalEntry::NonceChange { address } => {\r\n                    state.get_mut(&address).unwrap().info.nonce -= 1;\r\n                }\r\n``\r\nI would suggest we check if the nonce is greater than 0 like \r\n\r\n``rust\r\n  if let Some(entry) = state.get_mut(&address) {\r\n                        if entry.info.nonce > 0 {\r\n                            entry.info.nonce -= 1;\r\n                        }\r\n                    }\r\n``",
